law.text:
In addition to its other duties specified in this title, the State Advisory Board shall:
consult with and advise the Secretary on:
each aspect of the juvenile services program in the State;
the educational programs and services of the Department; and
programs designed to divert children from the juvenile justice system;
recommend to the Secretary policies and programs to improve juvenile services in the State;
participate in interpreting for the public the objectives of the Department; and
participate in planning the development and use of available resources to meet the needs of the Department.
